<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06266265 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06266265 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SPORT; QA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Q How does a tie figure into a team's winning percentage? For instance: The49ers finish the year with seven wins, eight losses and one tie. What's theirwinning percentage?; C. Chillkoot, Fremont  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  (NOT SO) DUMB QUESTIONS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Additional information attached to the end of this article.  </MEMO><TEXT>  A In this case, the 49ers would have a winning percentage of .469. A tiecounts as half a win and half a loss. You would divide the number ofvictories, 7.5, by 16, the total number of games played. Before 1972, the NFLdid not recognize ties and the winning percentage of a 7-8-1 team would havebeen .467.; SPORTS FACT; Longest reign by a heavyweight boxing champion; JoeLouis of the United States was champion for 11 years, 252 days. During hisreign, Louis defended his title a record 25 times.; SOURCE: Guinness Book ofSports Records 1991; Knight-Ridder News Service  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910922  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  148  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, September 22, 199100266265,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>